description: Strict Egyptian numbers - there is a unique representation of 1 as the sum of distinct unit fractions with the sum of denominators being these numbers.
links: Index entries for sequences related to Egyptian fractions
example: 1=1/2+1/3+1/6, 2+3+6=11, there is no other representation of 1 as the sum of distinct unit fractions whose numerators sum to 11, so 11 is in the sequence.
author: _Jud McCranie_, Dec 16 1999
extensions: No other terms <= 200. Is the sequence finite?
